cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with fine-grained recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a reinforcement learning framework for optimizing local discriminative regions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions benchmark datasets, which suggests that it involves experimental evaluation (cs.MM) and possibly natural language processing (cs.CL) if the datasets involve textual descriptions.
